.TH "scp_ipi_send" 9 "scp_ipi_send" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scp_ipi_send \- send data from AP to scp.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scp_ipi_send
.BI "(struct mtk_scp *scp "  ","
.BI "u32 id "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "scp" 12
mtk_scp structure
.IP "id" 12
IPI ID
.IP "buf" 12
the data buffer
.IP "len" 12
the data buffer length
.IP "wait" 12
number of msecs to wait for ack. 0 to skip waiting.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is thread-safe. When this function returns,
SCP has received the data and starts the processing.
When the processing completes, IPI handler registered
by scp_ipi_register will be called in interrupt context.

Returns 0 if sending data successfully, -error on error.
